00033 std::string
00034 SgAsmFunction::reason_str(bool do_pad, unsigned r)
00035 {
00036     using namespace StringUtility; // for add_to_reason_string()
00037     std::string result;
00038 
00039     /* entry point and instruction heads are mutually exclusive, so we use the same column for both when padding. */
00040     if (r & FUNC_ENTRY_POINT) {
00041         add_to_reason_string(result, true, do_pad, "E", "entry point");
00042     } else {
00043         add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_INSNHEAD), do_pad, "H", "insn head");
00044     }
00045 
00046     /* Function call:
00047      *   "C" means the function was detected because we saw a call-like instructon (such as x86 CALL or FARCALL) or instruction
00048      *       sequence (such as pushing the return value and then branching) in code that was determined to be reachable by
00049      *       analyzing the control flow graph.
00050      *
00051      *   "c" means this function is the target of some call-like instruction (such as x86 CALL or FARCALL) but could not
00052      *       determine whether the instruction is actually executed.
00053      */
00054     if (r & FUNC_CALL_TARGET) {
00055         add_to_reason_string(result, true, do_pad, "C", "function call");
00056     } else {
00057         add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_CALL_INSN), do_pad, "c", "call instruction");
00058     }
00059 
00060     if (r & FUNC_EH_FRAME) {
00061         add_to_reason_string(result, true,                 do_pad, "X", "exception frame");
00062     } else {
00063         add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_THUNK),     do_pad, "T", "thunk");
00064     }
00065     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_IMPORT),        do_pad, "I", "import");
00066     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_SYMBOL),        do_pad, "S", "symbol");
00067     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_PATTERN),       do_pad, "P", "pattern");
00068     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_GRAPH),         do_pad, "G", "graph");
00069     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_USERDEF),       do_pad, "U", "user defined");
00070     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_PADDING),       do_pad, "N", "padding");
00071     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_DISCONT),       do_pad, "D", "discontiguous");
00072     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_LEFTOVERS),     do_pad, "L", "leftovers");
00073     add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_INTRABLOCK),    do_pad, "V", "intrablock");
00074 
00075     /* The miscellaneous marker is special. It's a single letter like the others, but is followed by a fixed width
00076      * integer indicating the (user-defined) algorithm that added the function. */
00077     {
00078         char abbr[32], full[64];
00079         int width = snprintf(abbr, sizeof abbr, "%u", FUNC_MISCMASK);
00080         snprintf(abbr, sizeof abbr, "M%0*u", width, (r & FUNC_MISCMASK));
00081         abbr[sizeof(abbr)-1] = '\0';
00082         if (!do_pad) {
00083             std::string miscname = stringifySgAsmFunctionFunctionReason((r & FUNC_MISCMASK), "FUNC_");
00084             if (miscname.empty() || miscname[0]=='(') {
00085                 snprintf(full, sizeof full, "misc-%u", (r & FUNC_MISCMASK));
00086             } else {
00087                 for (size_t i=0; i<miscname.size(); ++i)
00088                     miscname[i] = tolower(miscname[i]);
00089                 strncpy(full, miscname.c_str(), sizeof full);
00090             }
00091             full[sizeof(full)-1] = '\0';
00092         } else {
00093             full[0] = '\0';
00094         }
00095         add_to_reason_string(result, (r & FUNC_MISCMASK), do_pad, abbr, full);
00096     }
00097 
00098     return result;
00099 }

00139 size_t
00140 SgAsmFunction::get_extent(ExtentMap *extents, rose_addr_t *lo_addr, rose_addr_t *hi_addr, NodeSelector *selector)
00141 {
00142     struct T1: public AstSimpleProcessing {
00143         ExtentMap *extents;
00144         rose_addr_t *lo_addr, *hi_addr;
00145         NodeSelector *selector;
00146         size_t nnodes;
00147         T1(ExtentMap *extents, rose_addr_t *lo_addr, rose_addr_t *hi_addr, NodeSelector *selector)
00148             : extents(extents), lo_addr(lo_addr), hi_addr(hi_addr), selector(selector), nnodes(0) {
00149             if (lo_addr)
00150                 *lo_addr = 0;
00151             if (hi_addr)
00152                 *hi_addr = 0;
00153         }
00154         void visit(SgNode *node) {
00155             if (selector && !(*selector)(node))
00156                 return;
00157             SgAsmInstruction *insn = isSgAsmInstruction(node);
00158             SgAsmStaticData *data = isSgAsmStaticData(node);
00159             rose_addr_t lo, hi;
00160             if (insn) {
00161                 lo = insn->get_address();
00162                 hi = lo + insn->get_size();
00163             } else if (data) {
00164                 lo = data->get_address();
00165                 hi = lo + data->get_size();
00166             } else {
00167                 return;
00168             }
00169 
00170             if (0==nnodes++) {
00171                 if (lo_addr)
00172                     *lo_addr = lo;
00173                 if (hi_addr)
00174                     *hi_addr = hi;
00175             } else {
00176                 if (lo_addr)
00177                     *lo_addr = std::min(*lo_addr, lo);
00178                 if (hi_addr)
00179                     *hi_addr = std::max(*hi_addr, hi);
00180             }
00181             if (extents && hi>lo)
00182                 extents->insert(Extent(lo, hi-lo));
00183         }
00184     } t1(extents, lo_addr, hi_addr, selector);
00185     t1.traverse(this, preorder);
00186     return t1.nnodes;
00187 }
